I have followed you. Follow me back

The kids go back to school this week, who’s happy?
I think it’s good for the kids to get back to some semblance of normalcy. It’ll also be good for their mental health.
I think we’ve all learnt a lot throughout this lockdown period, both about our children and ourselves. We’ve also had time to evaluate what/who is important to us and our kids. 
I know it’s not going to be ‘back to normal’ for the foreseeable, but this is a good start isn’t it?
I also think that while the situation was obviously awful, getting to spend that amount of extended time with our kids was something that not many other generations will have had/get in future. I think most of us have embraced it, for the most part. Of course there’s been ups and downs, but I think we’ve all got through it together. 
How are you/your kids feeling about going back this week?
